crypto.description:
Old Professor Benson has left this message behine, we thing it has a flag. 

Can you decrypt it and get the message he left behind for us?


Developed by ihanna2
crypto.name: B1nary Bens0n

crypto.description:
I asked ChatGPT to tell me a joke, but it's encoded. Can you figure out what it is?

> V2h5IGRpZCB0aGUgdG9tYXRvIHR1cm4gcmVkPwoKQmVjYXVzZSBpdCBzYXcgdGhlIHNhbGFkIGRyZXNzaW5nIQ==

Format: nicc{words can be spaced}

Developed by [ch0p](https://www.github.com/jozicoates)
hints: Enter the decoded text as "nicc{}"
crypto.name: Tell Me a Joke

crypto.description:
One of our members found this code in a lab. It looks like it was sent from a different time, I think the date said the year 8 AD...

> **Q ammuml bw pidm nwcvl ugamtn qv bpm Zwuiv Muxqzm bquma, Q lw vwb zmumujmz nwz Q owb pmzm, jcb Q vmml bpm ntio bw nqvl wcb pwe bw omb jiks bw xzmamvb lig! Wp twws, bpqa kwctl jm bpm ntio! vqkk{0vtg_b1um_e1tt_b3tt}**

It's encrypted, but how do we get the right answer...

Developed by [jackzabbs](https://github.com/JohnZabriskie)
hints: Maybe they were a fan of ancient Roman emperors.
crypto.name: Hours Behind

crypto.description:
Some of the NICC members were trying to get away camping after midterms, but all of their headphones immediately started blaring this sound when they tried to leave campus.  

Someone grabbed a recording, maybe we can piece it together?

Format: nicc{words_separated_by_underscores}

Developed by [ch0p](https://www.github.com/jozicoates)
hints: Maybe it's a cry for help or a warning. Who knows.
crypto.name: What's camping without s'morse

crypto.description:
Keys are hard to memorize, especially with tests coming up. 

I guess whoever has been breaking in around campus is struggling to keep things straight, too.

We found a message left up on a terminal with a post it next to it. 

We *think* it might be a key to solving the message that was left up, but haven't cracked it just yet. Think you could?

> lmq_chc_ur_mpq_jnbgvx

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
crypto.name: Dear Tom

crypto.description:
So we found this on a thumbdrive.
I know, I know, don't load random USBs, but look... 
Things are weird right now and I figured it might be something.

All it has is this half of a program and a weird mashing of letters and numbers.

Maybe it's nothing, but it might be something. Think you can check?

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
crypto.name: A new hope

forensics.description:
This photo was given to us and we believe this man may play an important part into all this craziness. Can you find out what the make and model of the device used to take the selfie was?
Flag will be in this format 

> nicc{MakeWord1_MakeWord2_ModelWord1_ModelWord2}

Developed by ihanna2
hints: Do photos save device info?
forensics.name: Say Cheese!

forensics.description:
This image was warped through time and something must have happened to it as we an no longer see it!

Can you help us so we can see the image?


Developed by ihanna2
hints: Restore the image to how it should be with some magic.
forensics.name: Warped Image

forensics.description:
We've been monitoring data coming and going from around campus. Might be worth looking into it to see if anything weird stands out.

Could be that's how whoever is behind the weird stuff on campus is communicating? We're looking for something from someone named RB.

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
hints: Filters might be handy...
forensics.name: No Expectation of Privacy

misc.description:
- `strings` & `objdump` are good friends, maybe they will be useful.

Developed by [AOrps](https://github.com/AOrps)
hints: What do you know about the file?
misc.name: strings_rev

hints:
Write your flag as nicc{firstname_lastname}.
All words are lowercase.
misc.name: How Expected

misc.description:
We found this zip file but its encrypted so we can't read the contents. Do you think you could crack it?

Developed by ihanna2
hints: We have this wordlist of commonly used passowrds today. Perhaps people in the future still use the same passwords?
misc.name: Old Habits Die Hard

misc.description:
We're happy to have you here. But, as with all time-travel, it's important to not break things.

Remember the rules of the guidebook. If you forgot, you're always welcome to [reference](https://discord.gg/p9wezJfzym) it.
hints: This is a standard gimme challenge. Go check out the discord!
misc.name: Welcome Travelers

misc.description:
Thanks for tuning in - We'll be back from the past in the future. For now, to get the flag, let us know your thoughts:

https://forms.gle/WRsYdAYHE9Zx2pBp9
misc.name: It's not goodbye

misc.description:
Look, I don't know what's going on. I'm in a room with a lot of skeletons and there's weird music coming from everywhere. One second I'm walking out of Kupfr, the next I'm in Hazell Center (???!!!), and now it's some room that's decorated for Halloween. It's St. Paddy's Day soon, what gives????

	1ab9ed9ccd962612b2407009132dabde

Developed by [CyberSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
misc.name: We're Jumping Timelines, Bud

osint.description: Bots have been using a program to go back into time and disrupt our current timeline. They have joined all the known web forums, including this Discord! Can you figure out who this culprit is and expose them? They have been reported to been named after a movie.
hints: Maybe there are some recent arrivals watching our activities on the discord...
osint.name: Who's there

osint.description:
Two of our members, Simon and Anna were arguing about where's better to take notes.

Simon thinks that Github isn't the best place to take your notes because you might leave something public behind by accident, like maybe a note about someone you didn't want public.

Anna disagrees because you can just delete it and recommit anyway, and it looks good to be active on Github!

Simon reminded them that we can see the changes... even what they wrote about Tom.

Anna rushed off, but now we're not sure what they're talking about. Could you figure it out?


Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
hints: Don't forget to wrap what you find in nicc{}
osint.name: Paper Digital same diff to me

osint.description:
There's rumors of a love triangle on campus and we *hate* not knowing things.

All we know is that it might be between some faculty or maybe staff or maybe students who just really can't let go of the past.

The only two solid pieces of information we got were "heroic_tom" and witches, which really doesn't make sense. 

Developed by [royCardigan](https://github.com/rickyhernandez1000)
hints: Have you checked social media?
osint.name: The Love Triangle

osint.description:
Students often blame bad teachers for bad grades and having to take extra semesters here at NJIT. Some wish they could go back in time to fix what went wrong. What if the fault wasn't a lack of studying? What if their bad luck was caused by something beyond their control?

We should look into it and see what we can find out.

Developed by [royCardigan](https://github.com/rickyhernandez1000)
hints: I bet somebody did some investigative reporting on this at one point or another
osint.name: Tick-Tock

osint.description:
We went out last night to party during spring break, or was it a few nights from now or the other day we went out?
Look, I don't know. It's spring break.
All I know is this dude Arbys was buying drinks and then next thing I know:
Bam, wake up and everybody's all weird. Can you come get me?
Anna's god knows where, but I'll help you find her if you find me.
No idea where I am though.
Here's a pic of a super shady atm by the bar I woke up in front of. 
Everything's closed but I think we sang here last night. 

Find when I created this and where I am. No spaces, no cases.
flag format nicc{yyyymmddbarname}

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
osint.name: Ow, my head

osint.description:
It looks like things at NICC have started to settle down, but this was child's play. 

I heard yesterday that next month brings something harder.

We better prepare and gather our resources if we're going to make it!

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
hints: Maybe there's another event coming.
osint.name: To the future!

osint.description:
One of our members sent us a message, but we're confused.
Why? Because it was sent around 96 years ago.
They said they were up late studying in VanHouten Library, got a call from Anna & Simon to come sing with them in the city.
Except, they never got to Penn Station that night.
They arrived to Penn Station, but in 1927. After that, I guess it's history.
At least she got to be in a performance!

flag format:
nicc{Name_Of_The_Performance}

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
hints: Not too many colleges accepted women in the 1920s near NYC.
osint.name: Hopping By Grace

osint.description:
Time is a construct, but apparently, cubes are not.
If I'm stuck a couple of weeks 21 years ago, I might as well make a few bucks.
Because I'm way back in time and my credit cards haven't even been created yet...
Mr. Ray said he'd pay $1,000 to disprove his whackyness.
I think I can do it. If I fail, I'll make it back as time progresses.
If I pass, hey, maybe I'll pass Physics with Libby.

Wrap the first sentence (not the title) of the page in nicc{}, replacing spaces with _.

nicc{The_first_sentence_says_this.}


Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
osint.name: We don't what

steg.description:
Ugh, why do they keep trying to make good music sound bad?
There's NO way this is what the DJ intended to play.
I can't believe they had the audacity to do this!


Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
steg.name: Everybody's SO Creative

steg.description:
Decode the coded message in the jpg file!


Developed by [theamazins17](https://github.com/theamazins17)
steg.name: Great Scott!
Odd Transmission

steg.description:
This pic we recovered from a lab pc seems suspect.

Can you check it out and see if anything stands out?



Developed by [jackzabbs16](https://github.com/JohnZabriskie)
steg.name: Backward Time

hints: If you DM me for hints you're gonna get gifs
steg.name: plainsight

steg.description:
It was all so peaceful, the drive out to Indiana, and it was going great until some guy hit me and then took off. 
I went to send a picture of the damange to my mechanic, and it got all pixilated and messed up when he got it. Oh well. I hope he finds what the car needs to be fixed.
hints: Maybe theres a hint inside my car?
steg.name: Crashed Bad

web.description:
This webpage seems to block any attempts at viewing the flag file. It seems to be using an htaccess file to block our requests. Is there anyway you can find a way to bypass this?

Developed by [J0RDANI](https://github.com/J0RDANI)
web.name: Apache Ain't So Bad

web.description:
Seems we're unable to access our important admin portal. It worked perfectly fine when we were at our headquarters. Can you help us out? Try to gain access to the admin page and find the secret key!

Developed by [J0RDANI](https://github.com/J0RDANI)
hints: The admin page may only be accessed by people on the local computer
web.name: HOSTile Takeover

web.description:
Here’s an archive of the original NICC website from when we used to be hosted by Geocities! (Cut us some slack, it was 1998.)


Developed by drodrii
hints: Looks like we were pretty early adopters of JavaScript too.
web.name: NICC 98

web.description:
With all of the weirdness happening around campus, we wanted to make sure we stop robots from crawling around where they don't belong.

Unfortunately, it was... misconfigured... by an over-eager web member who thought they should use 1337speak instead since they were dealing with robots.

Even worse, they left it on our old site from 1998 somehow!

Developed by [Cyb3rSw0rd](https://github.com/AlfredSimpson)
hints:
Why w0uld y0u wr1t3 in 13375p3@k?

Some people think hackers need to write like that, I guess?
web.name: Th3y d0nt sp3@k 1337
